codeparam.initial_display:
// Calculate the distance to move in both x and y directions.
// Assume that the int variable dist has been declared to store
// the distance to move and the double variable rotationInRadians 
// has also been declared to store the current rotation angle of 
// the car in radians.
// The current assignment to distX and distY will only move the car 
// in the X direction for the distance to move.

double distX = dist;
double distY = 0.0;

div.p:
Sample Answer


      double distX = dist * Math.cos(rotationInRadians); 

      double distY = dist * Math.sin(rotationInRadians);
